      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS KEEDS (8) did a great job to score by a long neck over this course and distance last start. Up in grade but plummets in the weights after the claim and expected to measure up again. CHEROKEE DANCER (1) hasn't raced since a win at Launceston over 1120m six-and-a-half weeks ago. Kept ticking over with a recent trial at Longford. Well placed this grade and looks hard to beat again. BOLD INSTINCT (5) was well off best over 1150m at this track last time out. Winning rider back aboard and best figures measure up. THOROS OF MYR (3) ran a much improved race second-up when placed here last time. Likely improver with winning claims. THE LONGEST YARD (4) might find this a shade sharp fresh but will wind up late and can sneak into the finish at odds.",
